AO.notes:
Visitors who have been granted an online pre-visa or have requested such pre-visa from the consulates of Angola abroad, are then issued with a visa on arrival at the country's border check points.
For a maximum total stay of 90 days within a one year period.
Besides having printed confirmation that a visa will be issued upon arrival, passengers must: have a return/onward ticket, and have a hotel reservation confirmation.

CU.notes: Tourist card in advance via travel agency, airline or at the embassy.

DO.notes: Visa not required for Algerians with a valid multiple entrance schengen visa for a maximum stay of 180 days

EG.notes: Visa not required for Algerian citizens under the age of 14.

ET.notes:
Visa on arrival is obtainable only at Addis Ababa Bole International Airport.
eVisa holders must arrive via Addis Ababa Bole International Airport.
eVisas are available for 30 or 90 days.

GA.notes: Electronic visa holders must arrive via Libreville International Airport.

GM.notes: In addition to a visa, an entry clearance must be obtained from the Gambian Immigration prior to travel.

KR.notes: Visa-Free access to Jeju Island for 30 days

MX.notes: Visa not required for Algerians with a valid multiple entrance schengen visa for a maximum stay of 180 days

PK.notes:
Online Visa eligible.
Electronic Travel Authorization to obtain a visa on arrival for business purposes.

SO.notes: Available at Bosaso Airport, Galcaio Airport and Mogadishu Airport.

TJ.notes: E-visa holders can enter through all border points.

TR.notes: Those below 18 or over 35 years old may obtain a visa online

UZ.notes: 5-day visa free transit when in transit at the international airports on condition of holding a confirmed onward ticket for a flight to a third country.
